article.description: Sam Sessoms scored scored 19 points and distributed six assists and Binghamton beat Division III-member SUNY-Oneonta 90-69 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Sessoms leads Binghamton past D-III Oneonta 90-69
article.linkText: Sessoms leads Binghamton past D-III Oneonta 90-69
article.story: BINGHAMTON, N.Y. -- Sam Sessoms scored scored 19 points and distributed six assists and Binghamton beat Division III-member SUNY-Oneonta 90-69 on Tuesday night. Richard Caldwell Jr. had 12 points for Binghamton (4-3), which won its fourth consecutive game. Andres Rivera scored a career-high 27 points for the Red Dragons. Kameron Hickey and Ian Schultz each scored 10 points. Binghamton matches up against Loyola (Md.) on the road on Sunday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
